<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Multigenerational Living Needs a Real Bedroom, Not Just a Finished Room</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>A lot of the calls we get from Ashland come from families bringing a parent or adult child into the household and finishing the basement to give everyone their own space. It's a smart way to stretch a house without moving, but it only works if the room legally counts as a bedroom. That means a proper egress window, not just a bigger window or a nicer paint job.</p><p>Whether your home is a newer build off I-80 or one of the older houses closer to downtown Ashland, the basement windows that came with the house were almost never sized for a bedroom. Builders and past owners installed them to let in light and air, not to meet the fire-exit standard that Nebraska code requires once someone is sleeping down there.</p><p>We size and place the window to fit your framing plan, so the new bedroom works with the layout you already have instead of forcing a redesign.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Serving Ashland and the I-80 Corridor</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>Ashland sits along I-80 between Lincoln and Omaha, close to Mahoney State Park and the Platte River, and we work throughout the area, from the newer subdivisions on the edges of town to the historic homes near Main Street. Because Ashland draws buyers from both metro areas, we see a real mix of home ages and foundation types, and we've handled cut-ins on both.</p><p>Ashland falls under Saunders County code requirements, and we're familiar with what local inspectors expect to see, so permitting and inspection scheduling don't slow your project down.</p><p>No matter where in Ashland your home sits, you get the same process and the same <a href="/egress-window-cost/">written estimate</a> we use on every job.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:0 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto 56px;">
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,32px);margin:0 0 18px;">Planning a Basement Conversion in Ashland</h2>
    <div class="rich"><p>With Ashland growing steadily as a bedroom community for both Lincoln and Omaha commuters, we're seeing more homeowners finish basements they once used only for storage. Some are adding a bedroom for a growing family, others are creating a private suite for aging parents moving in.</p><p>We recommend scheduling the egress window early in your finishing project, before drywall and flooring go in, since the cut-in creates dust and debris that's much easier to manage in an open space. Getting the window placed first also lets your framing plan work around a known opening instead of the other way around.</p><p>Call us before you lock in your basement plans and we'll walk the space with you, free of charge.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>
<section style="padding:72px 24px;background:#EAF5FB;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="kicker">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(24px,3.5vw,36px);margin:0 0 32px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Do Ashland's newer homes off I-80 still need egress windows for basement bedrooms?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Yes. Builders in Ashland's newer developments size basement windows for an unfinished space, not a bedroom. Once you frame in a bedroom or suite down there, code requires a proper egress window and well before an inspector will sign off.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Can an egress window help with a multigenerational living setup in Ashland?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Yes. If you're finishing a basement so a parent, adult child, or extended family member has their own bedroom, an egress window is what makes that room legal to sleep in and gives everyone a safe second way out.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Does Lincoln Egress Windows handle permits for Ashland jobs?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Yes. Ashland falls under Saunders County code requirements, and we handle the permitting and coordinate the inspection so you don't have to track down the paperwork yourself.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e3ded4;border-radius:8px;padding:24px 28px;">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:18px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">What does an egress window cost for a typical Ashland basement?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#555;margin:0;">Cost depends on your foundation depth, well material, and whether we're cutting a new opening or replacing an existing window. We provide a free written estimate for every Ashland home, and you can see typical ranges on our <a href="/egress-window-cost/">egress window cost</a> page.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
